100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 9, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on disarmament and international security, amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the fallout from the Scopes Trial continued to resonate, with debates over evolution and education sparking nationwide discussions. Meanwhile, in India, Mahatma Gandhi's recent imprisonment for civil disobedience has intensified calls for independence from British rule.
